fields.title: Achill Island Sea Salted Caramel Fudge Brownies
fields.title_tag: Achill Island Sea Salted Caramel Fudge Brownies
fields.snippet: We love this recipe, and it is a huge hit at the Salt Dock Coffee here at Achill Island Sea Salt. The fudge is added to the brownie mix and scattered on top so it's fudgey, caramelly, sweet and salty - what more could you want?
fields.body:
Ingredients


  • 175g dark chocolate
  • 125g butter, cubed
  • 100g castor sugar
  • 50g light, soft brown sugar
  • 2 eggs
  • 1 tsp vanilla extract
  • 100g plain flour
  • 1/2 tsp of baking powder
  • Pinch of Achill Island Sea Salt
  • 60g Achill Island Sea Salted Caramel Fudge, chopped, plus some for decorating.

    • Method


    1. Preheat oven to 170C.
    2. Grease and line a 9 inch square baking tray.
    3. Melt the chocolate and butter in a heatproof glass bowl over a pit of simmering water, making sure the bowl does not touch the water below. Stir until smooth and combined and set aside to cool.
    4. In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs, sugar and vanilla until it is light and foamy.
    5. Sift in the flour, baking powder and salt and fold through until it is all combined.
    6. Add in the melted chocolate and chopped fudge and fold through until it is well mixed.
    7. Pour into the baking tray and bake in the oven for 18-20 mins.
    8. Remove from oven and cool on a wire rack.
    9. Scatter the rest of the chopped fudge over and enjoy.

fields.title: Pickled Cucumbers
fields.title_tag: Pickled veg are a great way to add flavour to things like salads and sandwiches and these pickled cucumbers are so quick and easy to do that we always have a jar of them in our fridge in the summer.
fields.snippet: Pickled veg are a great way to add flavour to things like salads and sandwiches and these pickled cucumbers are so quick and easy to do that we always have a jar of them in our fridge in the summer.
fields.body:
Ingredients

  • 1 cucumber finely sliced
  • 1 tbsp of Achill Island Sea Salt, plus extra for the cucumbers
  • 50g castor sugar
  • 200ml of Apple Cider Vinegar
  • 10 fennel seeds
  • Pinch of Chilli flakes

Method

  1. Add the finely sliced cucumbers to a bowl and sprinkle with a generous pinch of sea salt and toss. Leave for 10 mins, then rinse and drain.
  2. In a heavy based saucepan add the vinegar, sugar, sea salt and spices and bring to a simmer until the salt and sugar has dissolved, remove from heat.
  3. Add the cucumbers to a sterilised jar and pour over the cooled vinegar.
  4. Seal and leave to cool before placing in the fridge. Once open these will keep for about 1-2 weeks.

fields.title: Crispy Chickpeas
fields.title_tag: This is our favourite way to cook chickpeas and we make them at least once a week. They are great in a wrap with chopped tomatoes, avocado and pickled red onions, or on toast with red pesto. So good!!
fields.snippet: This is our favourite way to cook chickpeas and we make them at least once a week. They are great in a wrap with chopped tomatoes, avocado and pickled red onions, or on toast with red pesto. So good!!
fields.body:
Crispy Chickpeas

Ingredients

  • 1 can of chickpeas
  • 1/2 tsp of smoked paprika
  • 1/4 tsp cumin
  • 1/4 tsp of garlic granules
  • Pinch of chilli flakes (optional)
  • 1 tsp of Achill Island Salt Flakes - Natural or Smoked
  • 1 Tbsp of Olive Oil

Method

  1. Preheat the oven to 200C
  2. Drain and rinse the chickpeas and spread them out on a tea towel and pat dry - you want them to be as dry as possible so they will be extra crispy. If you have time you can do this a couple of hours before hand.
  3. Place the dried chickpeas in an oven proof dish and add the spices, sea salt and olive oil and toss.
  4. Place in the oven for 15-20 mins until the chickpeas are golden and crispy.

fields.head: Welcome to Deegagh Sea Salt
fields.body:
Here at Deegagh Sea Salt we aim to bring you the very best of what Irish Sea Salt have to offer,
straight to your doorstep!

fields.name: Achill Island Sea Salt
fields.description: Pure Irish sea salt harvested from the wild Atlantic waters of Achill Island. Its soft and flaky texture creates an intensity of flavour that will enhance any dish.

fields.name: Achill Island Seaweed Salt
fields.description: Achill Island Seaweed Salt is a mix of our pure white natural sea salt flakes (75%)  and Atlantic Wakame (Alaria esculenta) (25%) which is hand harvested by the Connemara Seaweed Company.This unique fusion of sea salt and seaweed will give an exceptional umami flavour to any dish.  We love it sprinkled over roast potatoes or veg, over soups and salads or in baking, such as breads and savoury scones. Its also great roasted with nuts and seeds for a little savoury snack.

fields.name: Achill Island Smoked Sea Salt
fields.description: Our Achill Island Smoked Sea Salt is hot-smoked with beech and oak and will bring the taste of a BBQ grill and Achill Island to some of your favourite dishes.

fields.name: Blackthorn Scotland Sea Salt
fields.description: At Blackthorn, we use 100% west coast sea water and nothing else. There are no illusions: no adding, no seeding, no bleaching, just pure Scottish sea salt. When you taste Blackthorn Salt you taste nature  the sea, the winds and the thorns.

fields.name: Orsay Sea Salt
fields.description: Original Orsay Sea Salt flakes blended with Scarabus Whisky, hot smoked slowly over whisky oak. The subtle whisky enhancement and the deep smokey flavour is brought to life when served over warm culinary dishes. Our natural Sea Salt flakes are harvested from the rapid waters off the coast of Orsay, a wee Island on the Isle of Islay. Fresh, clean and clear, a true taste of the Hebrides. Our Sea Salt comes packaged in a reusable and recyclable 85g glass jar, perfect for everyday home use.

fields.name: Halen Mon Pure Sea Salt
fields.description: Our new design branded ceramic  jar is the perfect container for our famous flakes. Keep it by the cooker or on the table and refill with our pouches. 100g of our Pure White Sea Salt is included with this purchase.

fields.name: Ardnahoe Malted Barley Smoked Sea Salt
fields.description: Original Orsay Sea Salt flakes hot smoked slowly over peated barley to create a unique creamy flavour. The subtle peatiness and underlying malt tones will transport your senses to Ardnahoes front door. Our natural Sea Salt flakes are harvested from the rapid waters off the coast of Orsay, a wee Island on the Isle of Islay. Fresh, clean and clear, a true taste of the Hebrides. Our Sea Salt comes packaged in a reusable and recyclable 85g glass jar, perfect for everyday home use.
